{"id":"2304.14809","submitter":"Benedikt Fesl","authors":"Benedikt Fesl and Nurettin Turan and Wolfgang Utschick","title":"Low-Rank Structured MMSE Channel Estimation with Mixtures of Factor\n  Analyzers","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"eess.SP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  This work proposes a generative modeling-aided channel estimator based on\nmixtures of factor analyzers (MFA). In an offline step, the parameters of the\ngenerative model are inferred via an expectation-maximization (EM) algorithm in\norder to learn the underlying channel distribution of a whole communication\nscenario inside a base station (BS) cell. Thereby, the wireless channels are\neffectively modeled on a piecewise linear subspace which is achieved by the\nlow-rank structure of the learned covariances of the MFA. This suits the\nlow-rank structure of wireless channels at high frequencies and additionally\nsaves parameters and prevents overfitting. Afterwards, the trained MFA model is\nused online to perform channel estimation with a closed-form solution of the\nestimator which asymptotically converges to the minimum mean square error\n(MMSE) estimator. Numerical results based on real-world measurements\ndemonstrate the great potential of the proposed approach for channel\nestimation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Apr 2023 12:35:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 May 2023 15:35:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-02"}
